      "message": "Good catch — done, and it surfaced a second, related bug.\n\ndefaultMajorForBase now consults localMF.DefaultMajorVersions() first (matching resolveReplacement at load time), falling back to the published view.\n\nBut fixing only that revealed that tidy still produced a broken local-module.cue: the replacement target is reached only through the replacement, so tidyRoots pruned it, leaving a replaceWith whose target was no longer recorded as a dependency (load then failed with \"must be listed as a dependency with a version\"). This affected the explicit-major case too, not just bare paths. tidyRoots now re-adds each replacement target as a root at its minimum-version-selected version, so the target is recorded as a dependency as the commit message promises.\n\nAdded cmd/cue/cmd/testdata/script/modtidy_bare_replace.txtar, which runs cue mod tidy on the bare-path setup, checks the rewritten module.cue/local-module.cue, exports, and runs cue mod tidy --check for round-trip stability. It fails without either fix.",
